Hello,


I am trying to do a Delegate test on class with SpyBean dependency,

```
    Delegate {
        @Inject
	 A a;
	      
          execute() {
	     a.execute();
	}
     }
```
	
```
   class TestSetUp {
        @SpyBean A a;
	@SpyBean B b;
		
	@Before
        public void setUp() {
          MockitoAnnotations.openMocks(this);
	}
  }
   class Test extended TestSetUp {
	  @Resource
          @InjectMocks
	  Delegate delegate;
	  
	  @Test
	  public void testDelegate() {
	    delegate.execute();
	  }
   }
  
```

In real implementation the class A inject class B and another classes.
```
    class A {
	    @Inject 
		B b;
		@Inject 
		C c;
		...
	}
```

In the test scenario I expected that the spy class A will contain a spybean object B, but all members of class a are null.
The spy object b in the Test is not null.
Why are all the members of the spy object a in the Test class is null?

```
versions used
spring-boot-test-2.6.4.jar
mockito-core-4.0.0.jar
mockito-junit-jupiter-4.0.0.jar
```

